caption:
POKEDEX #224   |   OCTILLERY, THE JET POKEMON 

Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it 
before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery 
spews ink to escape. The pitch-black ink that Octillery spits is also used for cooking.

title: well they finally did it
body:
For the first time a video game mobie is better then it’s gamer counter part. I look forward to Detective Pikachu 2 because I just finished the game and my goodness was it so mediocre. Plot makes so sense, the puzzle are horrible , all actions are just spam A and we don’t get a conclusion to his father. Not to mention the horrible acting .
Skip the game just get the movie.

title: Review: Detective Pikachu (the movie)
body:
Our own @iris_keyblade reviews the #DetectivePikachu movie! #moviereview

Is Pokémon: Detective Pikachu the very best video game movie, like no one ever was?

Well, the competition wasn’t exactly fierce.  But, yes.  Yes, it is. While I’m no longer the huge fan of Pokémon that I used to be, I had a good time watching this movie.

It’s interesting, based on the different reviews that I’ve read and watched, how many people don’t seem to realize that this “video game movie”…
